# Cloudflare Workers Static Assets cache rules — read from the assets root
# (dist/client/_headers). Default for assets is `max-age=0, must-revalidate`,
# so without these rules even fingerprinted bundles revalidate on every load.
#
# vinext auto-generates a _headers with only the /assets/* rule, but ONLY when
# this file is absent (it skips on fs.existsSync). Vite copies this public file
# into dist/client first, so vinext defers to it — meaning we must re-declare
# /assets/* here or fingerprinted bundles silently lose immutable caching.
#
# /assets/* and /vad/* are content-addressed: Vite fingerprints JS/CSS/fonts
# under /assets/, and the Silero VAD binaries under /vad/ are vendored per
# package version — the bytes behind a given filename never change, so they are
# safe to cache immutably. HTML stays on the default (revalidate) so deploys
# take effect; logos are not fingerprinted, so they get a short revalidatable
# window instead of `immutable`.

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/vad/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/logos/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=604800
